dictionary.description:
At languid flame the withered tongues of men
Whispered frightfully a name beyond ken.
But fit the cosmic-shadowed dancer saw
To grant their timeworn audience twilight's fall.

Behold, shattered carapace of mine flesh—
Behold! That which is dead shall live again!

Colors in hues too ill for mortal eyes;
Pulsing static, ichoric, breathless cries—
Echoed thunder, hollow ring: cloudless skies
Could not bear the curse of ancient demise—

And here, I rise. Smoldering with greater vice.

I turn, and burn; there will be nothing left
When I am sated. And all that is, shall rest
In ash and dust. Even time will forget
That once there was love. Hate. Perhaps regret.

Only hunger remains. For I alone
in dim memory recall the last that shone.

The ones before that showed me the way home.
dictionary.evolution:
This pleases me.
But not for long.
dictionary.summon:
Some are compelled to consume.
Others hunger to be devoured.
You'll know which one you are, soon enough.
